  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0dc4\u0ddd \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dda \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db8 \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Switching parties or shopping is not on my syllabus\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake, the former Minister of State who was pardoned by the President, stated in Colombo today (26) that he has not changed, he is not afraid and that switching parties or going shopping is not in his syllabus.",
        "Mr. Ramanayake also stated that he regretted that he was not able to comment in front of the media as per his old habits, having received a conditional pardon.",
        "He said this while attending a press conference at the opposition leader's office in Marx Fernando Mawatha, Colombo, that although he has lost that freedom as he spoke freely, he will carry his voice against fraud and corruption to the best of his ability.",
        "Mr. Ramanayake also mentioned that more attention will be paid to art activities in the coming period.",
        "He also said that he would like to thank President Ranil Wickremesinghe, Justice Minister Wijedasa Rajapaksa and everyone else for the freedom given to him.",
        "Mr. Ramanayake also said that he would like to express his gratitude to all the artists and politicians who dedicated themselves to him during the very difficult period of imprisonment due to the Corona epidemic.",
        "Mr. Ramanayake further said that he has a lot of love from the people and he will not lose that love given by the people for the privilege of blessings."
      ],
